# Vercel Web Analytics Configuration

## Summary
Successfully configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js App Router project by updating the Analytics component import to use the correct Next.js-specific package path.

## Changes Made

### Modified Files:
- **v2/src/app/layout.tsx** - Updated Analytics import path

## Implementation Details

### What Was Done:
1. **Fetched Latest Documentation**: Retrieved the most up-to-date installation instructions from the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart)

2. **Analyzed Project Structure**: 
   - Identified this as a Next.js 16.1.4 project using the App Router
   - Found that `@vercel/analytics` v2.0.1 was already listed in dependencies
   - Located the root layout file at `src/app/layout.tsx`
   - Discovered Analytics component was already being used but with incorrect import path

3. **Fixed Analytics Import**:
   - Changed: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react';`
   - To: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/next';`
   - This follows the official Next.js App Router documentation which specifies using `@vercel/analytics/next` instead of `@vercel/analytics/react`

4. **Verified Implementation**:
   - Installed all dependencies using `npm install`
   - Ran `npm run build` - Build completed successfully ✓
   - Ran `npm run lint` - No new errors introduced (existing linting issues are unrelated) ✓
   - Confirmed Analytics component is properly rendered in the root layout before the closing `</body>` tag

## Why This Change Was Needed

The project was already using Vercel Analytics but with an incorrect import path. According to the official Vercel documentation:
- **Next.js App Router** should use `@vercel/analytics/next`
- **React (non-Next.js)** should use `@vercel/analytics/react`
- **Next.js Pages Router** should also use `@vercel/analytics/next`

Using the correct import path ensures optimal integration with Next.js and proper tracking functionality.

## Next Steps for Deployment

After this PR is merged and deployed to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in your Vercel project dashboard (Analytics section)
2. After deployment, verify tracking is working by checking the browser Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/*`
3. Visit the Analytics dashboard to view metrics after user visits accumulate

## Notes
- The `@vercel/analytics` package (v2.0.1) was already installed in the project
- The Analytics component was already correctly positioned in the layout (before closing `</body>` tag)
- No additional configuration or environment variables are required
- Analytics will automatically start tracking page views once enabled in the Vercel dashboard
